snippet.textDisplay: Kudos to your team but considering external workshops to learn a few tricks from other trainers out of boxing could be beneficial. Here is a suggestion fighting right hand bangers like Wilder. If you study Ortiz Wilder 2 Ortiz was boxing well until he switched off. Notice his South Paw stance always at an acute angle with his right shoulder facing Wilder....however as soon as he walks into a position where he was more parallet to Wilder...that Wilderbeast took the shot. Can you switch South Paw fighting at an acute angle ? If so possible that way when Wilder throws his overhand right you outward block his right hand with your right hand ala Taekwondo Karate style well almost and catch him with a straight left. OR you can fight orthodox block with your left hand and a very straight right in doing so covering your left face with your left hand and you right face with your shoulder and the whole extended arm. There is also another option where you practice cross defence ala George Foreman but not exactly...when you Jab with your left your right hand, forearm and elbow covers across your face and you switch to right jab you arm travels underneath your coming left arm in the same defense position.
